<div id="review_1590317847" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1590317847" />
    <a title=" Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Jenn Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Schu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18916088-jenn-schu"><img alt=" Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Jenn Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Schu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1625589678p2/18916088.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1590317847?book_show_action=true">Mar 25, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title=" Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Jenn Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Schu" class="user" itemprop="url" name=" Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Jenn Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Schu" href="/user/show/18916088-jenn-schu"> Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Jenn Ƹ̴Ӂ̴Ʒ Schu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18916088-jenn-schu?shelf=themechallenge2016">themechallenge2016</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18916088-jenn-schu?shelf=history-non-fiction">history-non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1590317847" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16158367214651479624">What an amazing story! David von Drehle clearly spent a great deal of time researching his book which truly does commemorate those that were lost in this horrible work fire. He sets the stage for the working conditions, the movement among young women to be heard for improved worker safety and shorter work days. I&apos;m grateful for the light that von Drehle was able to shed on those that lost their lives, escaping the Mt. Vesuvius eruption to the pogroms in Russia, and coming to America for a better</span>
  <span id="freeText16158367214651479624" style="display:none">What an amazing story! David von Drehle clearly spent a great deal of time researching his book which truly does commemorate those that were lost in this horrible work fire. He sets the stage for the working conditions, the movement among young women to be heard for improved worker safety and shorter work days. I'm grateful for the light that von Drehle was able to shed on those that lost their lives, escaping the Mt. Vesuvius eruption to the pogroms in Russia, and coming to America for a better life and to help their families. And, it was beautiful that the author included all that were lost in the fire, a touching memorial.<br /><br />The author further set the stage by unveiling the corruption and misdeeds by those in power from Tammany Hall to the judge that should have recused himself from the case to the dishonorable attorney Max Steuber, whom desperately wanted to maintain his honor despite the cases he took on. Steuber, in my opinion, was only out for the win, and not for doing what was right.<br />It's unfortunate that Harris and Blanck never paid for their crimes, but those 146 lives weren't lost in vain. Due to this horrific event and the immediate outcry that followed, politicians quickly set to work to improve worker rights.<br /><br />I only hope that those that read this book take into consideration the points that von Drehle made regarding working conditions in other countries. Just because we have better protections doesn't mean that this is worldwide. I'm sure many countries set up factories in other countries with less protections to keep the profit margin high.<br /><br />Again a well developed account of the Triangle fire, I learned so much about worker rights, insurance claims, corrupt politicians, and the changing world at the turn of the century in the United States.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16158367214651479624" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

